  {
    "id": "c25d5869-4754-4f51-beb9-b3ee25a0c725",
    "sentence": "During that time, spurred by rising demand in China and a boom in biofuels, farmers invested heavily in new equipment and technology to meet this rising demand.",
    "source": "Agriculture and Community Banking",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2019-03-28",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0ec9fef1-41aa-4c3b-98da-f76a7bc75983",
    "sentence": "The banking agencies simply cannot regulate better or more effective supervision.",
    "source": "New Yearâs Resolutions for Bank Regulatory Policymakers",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2024-01-08",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5a5829fb-c55b-4aef-a145-6660266b174b",
    "sentence": "The Federal Reserve's various liquidity measures should help facilitate that process indirectly by boosting investor confidence and by reducing the risks of severe disruption during the period of adjustment.",
    "source": "Liquidity Provision by the Federal Reserve",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2008-05-13",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0fe0a622-666f-47c9-9aca-2a11ce00ad4d",
    "sentence": "The Federal Reserve is committed to working together with the other regulators to continue providing guidance and resources, like this workshop, to ensure that banks are appropriately managing cyber risk.",
    "source": "Welcoming Remarks",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2023-02-15",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2b715c9d-896b-46a3-9072-c717e75a3caa",
    "sentence": "Certain fiscal policies, particularly those that increase productivity, can increase the potential of the economy and help confront some of our longer-term economic challenges.",
    "source": "Longer-Term Challenges for the U.S. Economy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2016-11-21",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fdbd3c7c-2521-4a5f-ae02-fbefc1906c43",
    "sentence": "As one banker in Wyoming told me: \"Consolidation is a huge threat as larger banks can deliver at a far lower cost.\"",
    "source": "Community Banks Rise to the Challenge",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2020-09-30",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e13fa8fe-945f-4b42-a96a-a478f923c7f9",
    "sentence": "Will it continue? That will depend, in part, on whether AI delivers on the productivity increases that some believe it will bring.",
    "source": "Innovation at the Speed of AI",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2025-10-15",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e4dfcc64-d093-4962-82af-1e4d64c15ade",
    "sentence": "As in the advanced economies, unwinding the stimulative policies introduced during the crisis will require careful judgment.",
    "source": "Asia and the Global Financial Crisis",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2009-10-19",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "45d7bc7d-5240-4392-8696-fb994d5bb9a9",
    "sentence": "Asset price bubbles that are associated with credit booms present particular challenges, because their bursting can lead to episodes of financial instability that have damaging effects on the economy.",
    "source": "How Should We Respond to Asset Price Bubbles? ",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2008-05-15",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bc6985c1-b353-43ea-8de6-2c8b9791f3de",
    "sentence": "After the March FOMC meeting, the Committee said that it \"does not expect it will be appropriate to reduce the target range until it has gained greater confidence that inflation is moving sustainably toward 2 percent.",
    "source": "The Outlook for the U.S. Economy and Monetary Policy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2024-04-03",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1f8708d2-b3c9-4d50-bc7c-19e5d2f6c7d5",
    "sentence": "Though if we look more closely, we can see that three out of four community banks hold assets of less than $500 million.",
    "source": "A Conversation on Community Banking",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2019-02-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "235071b3-a52d-4297-9681-6d244bfbc183",
    "sentence": "Credit appears broadly available to small businesses with solid credit histories, although indicators point to some difficulties facing firms with weak credit scores and insufficient credit histories.",
    "source": "Financial Stability a Decade after the Onset of the Crisis",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2017-08-25",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1d94aa90-e219-443d-8c85-197845393c6d",
    "sentence": "But, again, the yield curve, like the interest rate futures strip, reflects not only expectations of the path of short-term interest rates, but also liquidity and term premium factors Thus, to extract signal about policy from noise in the yield curve, a term structure model is required.",
    "source": "Models, Markets, and Monetary Policy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2019-05-03",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0c83f440-e531-4182-ba60-6cc36c7f72f6",
    "sentence": "You can only try to be as prepared as possible for the opportunities, as well as the disappointments, that will come your way.",
    "source": "Remarks on Class Day 2008",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2008-06-04",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "64b284b7-19f2-47c5-8cc5-b28e460bcef4",
    "sentence": "However, the use of equity-based incentive compensation may not be effective in aligning the incentives of mid- and lower-level employees with the interests of the firm, because these employees may view the outcomes of their decisions as unlikely to have much effect on the firm or its stock price.",
    "source": "Incentive Compensation, Risk Management, and Safety and Soundness",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2009-11-02",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0947f1b6-db8b-4ae6-9615-fd05f7463508",
    "sentence": "Some key services were starting to be centralized in specific Districts with the establishment of \"product offices\" to provide uniform services to banks nationally.",
    "source": "Modernizing Federal Reserve Operations in the 21st Century",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2026-04-21",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6f0a30d1-ad1d-4eb8-8a78-878313beabb3",
    "sentence": "We recognize that each regulator directly sees only a part of the larger picture, and we are working to stitch these parts together so we can collectively see that larger picture and the risks it holds. For example, the Securities and Exchange Commission is examining the potential for liquidity strains at mutual funds, and the Commodity Futures Trading Commission is working to understand the use of derivatives to hedge risks associated with leveraged loans.",
    "source": "Business Debt and Our Dynamic Financial System",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2019-05-20",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "56a885cc-7565-4cdc-a409-d424ed3ebacf",
    "sentence": "If a bank has the model, it will be able to optimize its balance sheet for the day on which the stress test is to apply by shifting into assets for which relatively lower loss functions apply.",
    "source": "Departing Thoughts",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2017-04-04",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f9dae299-bfab-42f6-b4a1-fc42b87d7381",
    "sentence": "In addition to these well-known puzzles, are also a large number of puzzles across all asset markets that I will group under the common theme of risk harmonization. Risk-harmonization puzzles concern whether a given risk is priced the same way in all markets in which that risk is traded.",
    "source": "Asset-Pricing Puzzles, Credit Risk, and Credit Derivatives",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2007-03-22",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d97f5787-3c60-4e8b-881d-0f757b6e03be",
    "sentence": "The regulations for both of these programs are currently under development.",
    "source": "Fostering Innovation in Community Development Finance",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2011-05-10",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c7020f82-98d2-4791-aaed-3251d08dd9bd",
    "sentence": "Since 2010, payroll employment has increased by almost 16 million jobs, and the unemployment rate has fallen from 10 percent to 4.8 percent--in line with most estimates of the longer-run normal level (or natural rate) of unemployment and with the median estimate by FOMC participants in the December 2016 Summary of Economic Projections (SEP).",
    "source": "The Economic Outlook and Monetary Policy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2017-02-22",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bdd45aa5-df32-48ef-91d0-5fd2ee35c34e",
    "sentence": "Mindful of my time constraints, I will limit myself to identifying two.",
    "source": "Regulating Systemic Risk",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2011-03-31",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f7d43b49-c37f-43d9-9ee1-ccaf115ca0e4",
    "sentence": "A stress test is a critical part of the annual capital review.",
    "source": "Developing Tools for Dynamic Capital Supervision",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2012-04-10",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b9f23188-5fb8-42ec-ae99-bfcbf68d2f16",
    "sentence": "Mutual banks have existed since the early 1800s but have long faced limited capital options and restrictions on managing capital distributions. I have spoken about these issues in detail in the past, so I will not rehash them today.",
    "source": "Thoughts on the Economy and Community Bank Capital",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2025-08-09",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c5edb746-2f5c-41e7-b6f0-2e4856f61abe",
    "sentence": "But that doesn't mean that we shouldn't continue to try to at least limit the burden.",
    "source": "Opportunities to Reduce Regulatory Burden and Improve Credit Availability",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2012-01-13",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "23ba146c-0a18-4672-a3a7-27cad88597c5",
    "sentence": "At the Hutchins Center on Fiscal and Monetary Policy, The Brookings Institution, Washington, D.C. (via webcast)",
    "source": "COVID-19 and the Economy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2020-04-09",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "38b1d4b1-53e6-4cc8-a6c8-832d116103d1",
    "sentence": "This greater degree of monetary accommodation seems appropriate given the adverse effects on U.S. aggregate demand coming from the rise in the dollar, an associated weakening of foreign economic prospects, and other developments that have restrained spending and kept inflation undesirably low.",
    "source": "The Transmission of Exchange Rate Changes to Output and Inflation",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2015-11-12",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d699b6c0-9c21-4948-a439-b85085e758a1",
    "sentence": "Other factors point to a gradual increase in inflation.",
    "source": "Thoughts on Unconventional Monetary Policy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2013-06-27",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4f1531a6-c225-4dd9-8196-8ec5258218c2",
    "sentence": "The turnaround in growth in each country will hinge on success in controlling the virus and limiting economic scarring from the past year's downturn, as well as on available policy space, and underlying macroeconomic vulnerabilities.",
    "source": "U.S. Economic Outlook and Monetary Policy: An Update",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2021-03-02",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6c9b5105-06cf-4212-bb97-49f01ef61f25",
    "sentence": "Banking is not risk-free, and the goal of the regulatory framework is to support the safe and sound operation of banks, not to eliminate risk altogether.",
    "source": "Responsive and Responsible Bank Regulation and Supervision",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2023-06-25",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "62e83b46-4717-43be-9362-fb5a9a0b02a5",
    "sentence": "This could reverse when the AI productivity gains are more fully realized or if the labor market transition leads to a rise in income inequality, such that well-off consumers receive a larger share of income, which could lower the neutral rate, all else equal.",
    "source": "Opening Remarks for the âAI and Productivity across the Economyâ Panel",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2026-02-24",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7f85317a-ea38-4c99-b891-540d1cfd65a3",
    "sentence": "And, more recently, as restrictive monetary policy has put downward pressure on aggregate demand, the demand for labor has moderated.",
    "source": "Getting Closer",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2024-07-17",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a411030a-b3a4-4d2c-a48a-1ae94bd43f68",
    "sentence": "In corporate bond markets, issuance of speculative-grade bonds dropped off sharply as risk spreads widened.",
    "source": "The Recent Financial Turmoil and its Economic and Policy Consequences",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2007-10-15",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "46cb59e7-17e8-4070-aa55-f9af06ea8284",
    "sentence": "Although the economy is recovering, it is still operating well below potential and unemployment remains high.",
    "source": "Challenges for State and Local Governments",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2011-03-02",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f4376f5c-6ef2-4598-9417-5319ee485750",
    "sentence": "The qualitative assessment conducted as part of the 2018 and 2019 CCAR cycles found that most firms either meet or are very close to meeting the Federal Reserve's supervisory expectations for capital planning.",
    "source": "Stress Testing: A Decade of Continuity and Change",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2019-07-09",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d29f185c-38d2-4364-b4d9-76322422edc5",
    "sentence": "The evolution of financial markets and instruments and the increased importance of market liquidity for managing risks have made risk managers in both the public and private sectors acutely aware of the need to ensure that financial firmsâ risk-measurement and management systems are taking sufficient account of stresses that might not have been threatening ten or twenty years ago.",
    "source": "Financial Stability: Preventing and Managing Crises",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2007-02-21",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b0ebb789-b2e9-4cb2-a963-525c4f8a2d47",
    "sentence": "Improving the speed of payments, particularly retail payments, can be accomplished without the introduction of a CBDC.",
    "source": "Considerations for a Central Bank Digital Currency",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2023-04-18",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "878ef039-d7d7-4e55-b5c7-8704ebb576bb",
    "sentence": "And the downside risks to employment have increased.",
    "source": "Review and Outlook",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2024-08-23",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a97783c9-9e8b-41cb-988a-94ffde107ba8",
    "sentence": "It was the 11th consecutive month that inflation exceeded 2 percent.",
    "source": "Fighting Inflation with Rate Hikes and Balance Sheet Reduction",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2022-02-24",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "420198fc-9dec-42a4-8ea5-db5045cd7bde",
    "sentence": "These and similar issues will need to be addressed as options for minimum margins are further developed.",
    "source": "Shadow Banking and Systemic Risk Regulation",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2013-11-22",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "281596d6-098a-4f5b-94d9-21085e4d05d6",
    "sentence": "Inflation readings over the past several months have been surprisingly soft, however, and the 12-month change in core PCE prices has fallen to 1.3 percent.",
    "source": "The U.S. Economy and Monetary Policy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2017-10-15",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "69b8f1d2-4d7c-48fb-ae3f-e8a92cdd1923",
    "sentence": "For one, uncertainty about the outlook for government policy in health care, regulation, taxes, and trade can cause firms to delay projects until the policy environment clarifies.",
    "source": "The Low Level of Global Real Interest Rates",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2017-07-31",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "219244ec-e1f0-44f0-88ab-7d7f5f89c139",
    "sentence": "My colleagues and I strongly support the dual mandate and the equal weighting of objectives that it implies.",
    "source": "Federal Reserve Communications",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2007-11-14",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
