    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "18e8bcb3-ace6-402d-a67b-e98295dc02c1",
    "sentence": "We could probably spend the day arguing about the proper order of the outward progression of these circles, but I think we can all agree that at the core of a healthy bank is an effective corporate governance structure. A bank's board of directors should understand the bank's exposure to risk, and its members should be willing and able to critically question senior management about important matters affecting those risks.",
    "source": "Community Bankers and Supervisors: Seeking Balance",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2011-04-07",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
