  {
    "id": "96c89bf8-db02-4bad-a342-363a64e719dd",
    "sentence": "They assume that the target leverage of banks and others decreases, as it has in previous lending cycles, but they also net out reduced lending from one leveraged entity to another.",
    "source": "On \"Leveraged Losses: Lessons from the Mortgage Meltdown\"",
    "doc_type": "speech",
